# XXX not work for readonly documents
 from Products.ERP5.Document.Document import NotConvertedError
 from Products.ERP5Type.Utils import sleep
 
 portal_type = context.getPortalType()
 filename = context.getFilename()
 data = context.getData()
 content_type = context.getContentType()
 portal_type_empty_map = {
 "Spreadsheet": "XLSY;v2;2286;",
 "Text": 'DOCY;v5;39297;',
 "Presentation": "PPTY;v1;20344;",
 }
 portal_type_format_map = {
 "Spreadsheet": "xlsy",
 "Text": "docy",
 # "Presentation": "ppty",
 }
 file_format = portal_type_format_map.get(portal_type, None)
 if file_format:
 if data:
 if ((filename and not filename.endswith('.' + file_format)) or 
 not content_type.startswith("application/yformat.")):
 for try_count in range(3):
 try:
 metadata, data = context.convert(format=file_format)
 break
 except NotConvertedError:
 sleep()
 continue
 context.setData(data)
 context.setContentType(metadata)
 else:
 data = portal_type_empty_map.get(portal_type, None)
 if data:
 # portal_type_mime_map = {
 # "Spreadsheet": "application/yformat.xlsy",
 # "Text": "application/yformat.docy",
 # "Presentation": "application/yformat.ppty",
 # }
 context.setData(data)
 context.setContentType('application/yformat.' + file_format)
 if filename:
 new_filename = '.'.join(filename.split('.')[:-1]) + '.' + file_format
 if new_filename != filename:
 context.setFilename(new_filename)
 else:
 context.setFilename(context.getTitle() + '.' + file_format)
 return data
